1. Source Identity

Author: Traditionally attributed to Hermes Trismegistus

Work: Corpus Hermeticum (with awareness of the related Latin Asclepius, but treated separately)

Recommended scholarly edition

Brian P. Copenhaver (translation and notes)
Public-domain working text: The Divine Pymander (John Everard, 1650) or Thrice Greatest Hermes (G. R. S. Mead, 1906) for passage extraction. Modern translations should generally be paraphrased for copyright reasons.

Date

1st–3rd century CE (individual treatises likely composed over different periods).

Source status

Core philosophical Hermetic text.

Text type

Hybrid:

visionary revelation
philosophical dialogue
mystical theology
initiatory instruction

Primary extraction mode

Rather than extracting "arguments" alone, the engine should extract:

cosmological architecture
stages of initiation
anthropology
