8. Editorial Review

Keep:
Essays 2 and 4 are essential. They preserve what makes Picatrix different from purely philosophical Hermeticism: image and material operation.

Merge:
Do not create separate essays for every planet unless building a later reference atlas. Planetary material belongs inside Essay 4.

Split:
Book II should be split into image and timing. These are distinct enough to deserve separate essays.

Cut:
Cut any broad essay called “The Imaginal Cosmos” or “The World as Symbol.” Too vague.

Uncertain:
Book IV may need refinement after passage-pack extraction. It may become either one medium essay or a supporting conclusion to the capstone.

