Source Companion Blueprint: Éliphas Lévi — Dogme et Rituel de la Haute Magie
1. Source Identity

Author: Éliphas Lévi, born Alphonse-Louis Constant.
Work: Dogme et Rituel de la Haute Magie, translated by A. E. Waite as Transcendental Magic: Its Doctrine and Ritual.
Date: French work appeared in two volumes: Dogme in 1854 and Rituel in 1856; Waite’s English translation appeared in 1896.


Text type: Nineteenth-century occult synthesis; symbolic doctrine; ritual theory; magical rhetoric.
Public-access basis: Internet Archive has public-domain scans of the 1896 Waite translation and 1861 French editions.


Primary extraction mode: Extract symbols, will, astral light, imagination, polarity, Tarot correspondences, ritual logic, magical authority, and Lévi’s modern reframing of older occult materials.

2. Master Structural Reading

Lévi is not Agrippa. He does not simply catalogue the occult universe.

Lévi is the nineteenth-century converter: he turns older learned magic, Kabbalah, alchemy, Tarot, ceremonial ritual, and Catholic symbolism into a modern symbolic language of will, imagination, polarity, and astral light.

The structure is dual:

Doctrine / Dogme — what magic is, what the symbols mean, what powers underlie them.
Ritual / Rituel — how the doctrine becomes practice, discipline, invocation, consecration, and magical operation.

The core question is:

How does modern occultism become a symbolic science of will acting through astral light?

3. Part / Book Map
Part I — Doctrine

Function: Builds Lévi’s metaphysical and symbolic framework.
Main problems: What is magic? What is the astral light? What is the will? Why do symbols have power?
Key materials: magician, will, astral light, tetragram, Kabbalah, Tarot, equilibrium, universal agent.

Part II — Ritual

Function: Converts doctrine into ceremonial method.
Main problems: What must the operator become? How do consecration, evocation, initiation, and ritual discipline work?
Key materials: preparation, instruments, circles, conjurations, pentagram, necromancy, transmutation, magical images.

